'''Suwa Shrine''' (すわじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945}} located in Bessho-chō, {{ill|lt=Izumo City|Q825166|WD=Q825166}}, {{ill|lt=Shimane Prefecture|Q132751|WD=Q132751}}.

=== Overview ===
[[File:Bessho Suwa Jinja Keidai.jpg|thumb|Shrine grounds of Suwa Shrine|250px]]
The date of establishment is unknown, but there exists a {{ill|lt=munafuda|Q8008834|WD=Q8008834}} (ridgepole inscription) dating from {{ill|lt=Tenshō|Q1145058|WD=Q1145058}} 12{{sfn|Ashida, ed.|1930|p=272}}. There is a theory identifying this shrine with the “Izumo no Yashiro” recorded in the {{ill|lt=Izumo no Kuni Fudoki|Q11395858|WD=Q11395858}} and the “{{ill|lt=Izumo Shrine (Engishiki)||WD=|lt=Izumo Shrine}}” listed in the {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|WD=Q11064932}}{{sfn|Ashida, ed.|1930|p=272}}, but there are multiple candidate shrines for Izumo no Yashiro / Izumo Shrine, and criticism of the Suwa Shrine theory is strong{{sfn|Ishizuka|1986|pp=156–189}}.

In {{ill|lt=Meiji|Q3125096|WD=Q3125096}} 5 (1872), it was designated a village shrine{{sfn|Takahashi|1983|p=515}}.

=== Enshrined deities ===
'''{{ill||lt=Takeminakata-no-Kami|UNKNOWN}}'''
:According to the 18th-century topographical work {{ill||lt=Unyōshi|UNKNOWN}}, there was a rock cliff more than 40 ken high on Mount Miya, and beside it a round standing rock about 30 ken high and roughly 5 jō in circumference, called “Hobashira-ishi” or “{{ruby|檣|kachi|rp1=[|rp2=]}}-ishi”{{sfn|Ashida, ed.|1930|p=272}}{{efn|The Hobashira-ishi no longer exists{{sfn|Shimane Prefectural Shrine Association}}.}}. There is a tradition that when the monk Chishun, who founded {{ill|lt=Gakuen-ji|Q11674322|WD=Q11674322}} located near Suwa Shrine, came from {{ill|lt=Shinano Province|Q289250|WD=Q289250}}, three old men welcomed him by boat and then divided the ship’s fittings and flew off to three places{{sfn|Ashida, ed.|1930|p=272}}. One of them was Suwa Myōjin; the fitting he took was the mast, which is said to be the Hobashira-ishi{{sfn|Ashida, ed.|1930|p=272}}.

'''{{ill||lt=Yatsukamizuomitsuno-no-Mikoto|UNKNOWN}}'''
:The {{ill||lt=Unyōshi|UNKNOWN}} states “it is Takeminakata-no-Mikoto,” and does not list Yatsukamizuomitsuno-no-Mikoto{{sfn|Ashida, ed.|1930|p=271}}.

